# Data, Resources, Catalogs and IDs

## Applies when

Apply when creating, reviewing, or modifying ID constants, Resource schema scripts, `.tres` static definitions, catalogs, or catalog/resource validation tests. Priority: Critical.

## Source of truth

- `docs/prd/03_IDS_AND_CONSTANTS.md` owns canonical IDs, constant files, ID naming rules, validation errors, uniqueness requirements, and ID validation.
- `docs/prd/04_GAME_STATE_SCHEMA.md` owns the boundary between static Resources and runtime Dictionary state.
- `docs/prd/05_CARDS_DATABASE.md` owns CardDefinition schema, exact card membership, card prices, card types, destinations, and card Resource files.
- System owner PRDs own their Resource schemas and membership: roles, contracts, Street Deals, contacts, Turf Levels, and AI profiles.
- `docs/prd/15_GODOT_ARCHITECTURE.md` owns Resource catalog architecture, folder placement, catalog access patterns, and catalog tests.

## Static Resource Rule

- Store all static gameplay definitions as `.tres` Resources using their documented Resource schema.
- Keep `.tres` Resources immutable during gameplay.
- Resources define what exists; runtime Dictionary state stores what happened.
- Runtime state must store Resource IDs, counters, booleans, flags, and progress, not Resource instances.
- Resource schema scripts must extend `Resource`, use the documented `class_name`, and expose only PRD-owned fields.
- Do not add exported fields to a Resource schema unless the owner PRD is updated first.
- Do not create new `.tres` files, remove required `.tres` files, rename IDs, or change balance values unless the owner PRD explicitly changes the catalog membership or schema.

## Required Resource Schemas

Use the exact PRD-owned schema for each static definition type:

| Resource schema | Required location | ID owner |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `CardDefinition.gd` | `res://data/resources/cards/` | `GameIds.CARD_IDS` |
| `RoleDefinition.gd` | `res://data/resources/roles/` | `RoleIds.ALL` |
| `ContractDefinition.gd` | `res://data/resources/contracts/` | `ContractIds.ALL` |
| `ContactDefinition.gd` | `res://data/resources/contacts/` | `ContactIds.ALL` |
| `StreetDealDefinition.gd` | `res://data/resources/street_deals/` | `StreetDealIds.ALL` |
| `AIProfileDefinition.gd` | `res://data/resources/ai_profiles/` | `AIProfileIds.ALL` |
| `TurfLevelDefinition.gd` | `res://data/resources/turf_levels/` | `TurfLevelIds.ALL` |

- Every Resource ID must exactly match the corresponding constant value.
- Every Resource set must have exact catalog membership: no missing required definitions, no extra unowned definitions, no duplicate IDs.
- `TurfLevelDefinition.level` uses integers `0..10`; string Turf IDs are forbidden.
- AI profile ID `merchant` is valid only as an AI profile ID; `merchant_ai.tres` may have `id == "merchant"` as documented.
- Card Resources must preserve the exact 16-card MVP database, base prices, types, destinations, limits, and required files from `05_CARDS_DATABASE.md`.

## Catalog Access Rule

- Gameplay logic must access static Resources only through catalogs.
- Catalogs may preload or load known Resource files, validate IDs, return definitions by ID, return all definitions, and return all IDs.
- Required catalogs:

```text
res://logic/catalog/CardCatalog.gd
res://logic/catalog/RoleCatalog.gd
res://logic/catalog/ContractCatalog.gd
res://logic/catalog/ContactCatalog.gd
res://logic/catalog/StreetDealCatalog.gd
res://logic/catalog/AIProfileCatalog.gd
res://logic/catalog/TurfLevelCatalog.gd
```

- Catalogs must not own runtime state.
- Catalogs must not mutate Resources.
- Catalogs must fail safely for invalid IDs: return a documented null/safe failure or structured error without mutating runtime state.
- Missing required Resources, duplicate IDs, or invalid fields must fail catalog/resource tests instead of using runtime fallbacks.
- Logic modules outside `logic/catalog/` must not scatter-load `.tres` files with ad-hoc `load()`, `preload()`, `ResourceLoader.load()`, hardcoded paths, or directory scans.

## ID and Constants Rule

- Stable IDs and validation errors live in `res://data/ids/`.
- IDs must be lowercase `snake_case`, stable, untranslated, and free of spaces or hyphens.
- Use constants from the owner ID class instead of repeated raw gameplay strings.
- Each `ALL` array must contain every declared value in its domain exactly once.
- Do not create aliases, duplicate constants with different names for the same value, compatibility IDs, display-name IDs, translated IDs, or local duplicated ID lists.
- Do not rename IDs after Resources or tests exist.
- If a system needs a new ID, update the owner PRD and constants first, then Resources, catalogs, logic, tests, and UI selectors.

## Display Text Rule

- `title`, `description`, `effect_summary`, `limitation_summary`, option labels, and option descriptions are display text only.
- Gameplay logic must resolve behavior by canonical IDs and owner logic rules, not by parsing human-readable Resource text.
- UI may display summaries but must not parse summaries into gameplay behavior.

## Runtime State Boundary

- Do not store runtime state in Resources, `.tres`, catalogs, or Resource schema scripts.
- Do not store player ownership, market state, cooldowns, contract progress, debts, random state, combat logs, phase state, or gameplay flags in Resources.
- Runtime state must remain JSON-compatible Dictionary snapshots as defined by `04_GAME_STATE_SCHEMA.md`.
- Resource data may be read by logic and then expressed in runtime state only as IDs, counters, booleans, strings, arrays, or dictionaries.

## Forbidden behavior

- Do not mutate `.tres` Resources at runtime.
- Do not place runtime gameplay state in Resource instances.
- Do not add Resource schema fields without an owner PRD schema update.
- Do not add or remove catalog members without updating the owner PRD, constants, Resources, and tests together.
- Do not parse `description`, `effect_summary`, `limitation_summary`, labels, filenames, or display text as gameplay logic.
- Do not implement ad-hoc Resource loading from domain logic.
- Do not hardcode repeated gameplay IDs when a constant owns the value.
- Do not create aliases or fallback IDs for invalid, legacy, translated, or display-name values.
- Do not silently ignore missing required Resources, duplicate Resource IDs, wrong types, wrong prices, or missing required fields.
- Do not let catalogs depend on UI, scene nodes, runtime state managers, random helpers, or debug snapshots.
- Do not modify Resource instances returned by catalogs.
- Do not derive gameplay IDs from filenames, folder names, display names, or translated text.

## Required tests

Catalog and Resource tests must verify:

- every required Resource schema script exists;
- every required `.tres` file exists;
- every Resource loads successfully through its catalog;
- every Resource ID exists in the correct constants `ALL` array;
- every constants `ALL` array has no duplicates and exact expected membership;
- every Resource set has no duplicate IDs;
- every required exported field is present and valid;
- card base prices, types, destinations, and exact 16-card membership match `05_CARDS_DATABASE.md`;
- roles, contracts, contacts, Street Deals, AI profiles, and Turf Levels match their owner PRDs;
- invalid IDs return safe catalog behavior;
- catalogs do not mutate Resources;
- runtime state contains IDs and Dictionary data, not Resource instances.

## Output requirements

For data, Resource, or catalog changes, report:

- Owner PRD:
